PSTG reported a solid beat and raise qtr, with momentum in product and subscription. Macro commentary improved Q/Q and META is starting to rev rec, but the real monetization comes in FY27, where we are awaiting more details, likely to come at Sept A-Day. Sets move higher, as does our PT, to \(\) 72\$
July quarter beat was solid across the board, though Subscription revenue was \(2\%\) light of MSe. Nothing we'd worry about though.
New customer/logo wins highlight the 'data center modernization' opportunity in storage which mgmt believes is only in the 1st inning.
META rev rec a positive step forward, but don't expect much contribution this year. Expecting more details at Sept 25th Accelerate event.
RPO growth of \(22\%\) Y/Y accelerated from the last two quarters, helping to support total revenue growth accelerating in F2H.
PT moves to \(\) 72\(, or 29x our FY27 FCF/share of\) \ \(2.50\) , implying a largely balanced R/R, though with more upside bias to sets for the core (i.e. ex META) biz.

Tough to poke holes in that quarter; Increasing PT to \(\) 72\(through remain EW on valuation. PSTG reported a strong July quarter highlighted by an improving macro backdrop and broad - based strength in customer demand across Product and Subscription, though the product beat (+6%) was more notable vs. MSe than subscription (2% miss). Importantly, the strength in tonight's report wasn't isolated to F2Q, as management raised their full year revenue and operating income guidance, resulting in our 2H revenue and operating income both increasing 5% post - earnings. Stepping back, our positive July VAR checks played out in PSTG's results, with management highlighting a handful of new customer wins/expansions led by large enterprises, with strength across FlashBlade (Product revs up 11% Y/Y), Evergreen//One (TCV up 24% Y/Y) and Portworx (a number of new logo wins). PSTG's even started to recognize revenue on its META (covered by Brian Nowak) deployment, though the contribution to results was immaterial. Post- earnings, we are incrementally more positive on the PSTG story, with the 2Q beat/FY26 raise pushing our PT to \(\) 72\(from\) \ \(60\) ; or \(29x\) our new FY27 FCF/share of \(\) 2.50\(, though we recognize they need to deliver in the FY27 META deal, and expect more details to emerge at next month's Accelerate event.\)

\((\pm)\) Dark clouds dissipate as macro and micro improve in the July quarter. Management was notably more upbeat on the macro environment on tonight's call, acknowledging that the uncertainties from early in the quarter dissipated and that the 2H outlook "feels a lot better". However, that comment also encapsulates management's bullishness at the micro level as well, highlighting a robust pipeline and a data center modernization opportunity that might not even be in the first inning. As we alluded to earlier, our PSTG checks have been consistently strong, and this is clearly showing up in results/guidance, though the degree of 2H upside (positively) surprised us.

\((\equiv)\) Upside coming primarily from accelerating Product as Services momentum sustains. If there is one minor nitpick from tonight's results, it's that upside in the quarter came from Product, not Subscription, as Product growth accelerated 4 points vs. F1Q to \(11\%\) Y/Y while Subscription growth decelerated by 2.5 points vs. 1Q, and Subscription ARR Y/Y growth was unchanged Q/Q. However, we wouldn't harp on this dynamic too much, as subscription "attach" was stronger than we expected, and growth is still robust/accelerating.

\((\pm)\) Starting to recognize META deployments, but FY27 remains the period of "real" revenue. In what was a positive surprise, PSTG highlighted that they have started to deploy the first volumes to META and recognized the first revenue from this partnership in the July quarter, though management clarified the impact from META in 2Q was immaterial. Looking forward, the 1- 2EB pilot deployment target is still on track for FY26, though mgmt also hinted at the potential for "possibly more", though we believe this is more so management expressing confidence in delivering on- target in FY26 vs. pulling forward any of the real deployment (double digit EB's) expected to come in FY27. Management did not share any further details on META monetization expectations, and thus we look to Pure//Accelerate in September as the next event where we could learn more on exactly how to size this opportunity.

AFA leadership expands to new markets. Pure gains incremental share from Al and hyperscaler traction, as penetration of TAM increases on the back of new products, end markets. FY27 FCF per share is \(13\%\) higher than in our base case, as Al drives additional demand for power saving technologies and storage demand environment improves despite tariffs. Stock trades at 40x FY27E FCF per share, more in line with software companies and gives credit to Al story and cloud growth potential.

Some benefit from Al story/cloud growth potential. Traction across the portfolio drives growth in FY26. Subscription and cloud offering growth continues to improve, providing NT headwind to growth. Operating leverage scales. Our 29x FY27E FCF per share is about the level of its historical average of 28.5x.

Competitive environment heats up and macro/tariffs takes enthusiasm out of growth story. FY26 growth challenged as macro causes customer budget tightening, particularly with tariffs and competition intensifies. The hyperscaler deal proves smaller than initially anticipated and limited traction made with other hyperscaler customers. FCF per share multiple is more in- line with infrastructure peers.
